description: Elon Musk responded to allegations of 'anti-white propaganda' in Netflix's Adolescence series. The claims, regarding race-swapped characters and a misleading narrative, were debunked by co-writer Jack Thorne, emphasizing the show is not based on a true story and focuses on issues of masculinity.
title: Elon Musk slams Netflix series Adolescence, co-writer replies

description: Union Minister Pralhad Joshi criticizes the Karnataka government for imposing a garbage cess in Bengaluru. BJP leaders claim the Congress-led government is taxing everything due to financial mismanagement. Protests are planned against the price hikes in essentials like milk, electricity, and now waste management fees. The new garbage tax is set to burden residents and businesses from April 1.
title: 'Garbage for nation': Karnataka govt faces flak over waste collection fee

description: State Bank of India (SBI) services are currently experiencing downtime, impacting mobile banking, ATM withdrawals, and fund transfers. The disruption, which began around 8:15 am, is attributed to annual closing activities scheduled between 1:00 pm and 4:00 pm today. SBI advises using UPI Lite and ATM channels during this period. NPCI also notes potential intermittent transaction declines.
title: SBI outage: Users report facing issues with mobile banking, fund transfers
SC rejects plea against HC order allowing whitewash of Jama Masjid wall in Sambhal

description: The Supreme Court condemned Uttar Pradesh and Prayagraj authorities for illegally demolishing houses without due process, violating residents' Article 21 rights. It ordered Rs 10 lakh compensation for affected owners. The demolitions were reportedly based on mistaken assumptions about the land's ownership.
title: 'Shocks our conscience': SC slams UP govt over 'illegal' demolition of houses

description: An explosion from a ruptured gas pipeline near Kuala Lumpur ignited numerous residences, affecting over 100 individuals during Eid. The fire, visible for hours, damaged 49 houses and hospitalized 63 people. Selangor's Chief Minister confirmed evacuations, with temporary housing in mosques. Emergency services isolated the pipeline and initiated investigations.
title: Watch: Gas pipeline explosion in Malaysia sparks massive fire, over 100 injured

description: Two goods trains operated by NTPC collided in Jharkhand's Sahebganj district, resulting in the deaths of both drivers and injuring four others. The incident occurred on NTPC-owned tracks used for coal transportation, linking their power plants in Bihar and West Bengal. The collision happened near Bhognadih in the Barhait police station area around 3 am.
title: 2 loco pilots dead, 4 injured as goods trains collide head-on in Jharkhand

description: Ashwani Kumar made an impressive debut in the IPL, taking four wickets in his spell against Kolkata Knight Riders, including dismissing their captain and the powerful Andre Russell. He is now the first Indian bowler to achieve such a feat on IPL debut, playing a crucial role in his team's victory.
title: Ashwani Kumar: From forgotten name to record-setter on IPL debut
'Can't shut someone's mouth': Yogi reacts to rift speculation with central leaders

description: The USCIS has completed the FY 2026 H-1B visa cap selection, with enough registrations to meet the limit. Selected applicants can file their petitions from April 1, 2025, provided they submit within the designated period and include the necessary documents.
title: H-1B selection for FY 2026 complete: Here’s how to check your status

description: A Lamborghini crash in Noida highlights the issue of reckless driving of luxury cars in India. The driver, Deepak Kumar, was arrested but later released on bail. Similar incidents in Nagpur, Mumbai, Pune, and Ahmedabad involving high-end cars driven recklessly have resulted in fatalities and serious injuries, raising concerns about road safety and accountability.
title: Supercars go rouge: From Lamborghinis to Porsches, when luxury turns dangerous

description: Samajwadi Party chief Akhilesh Yadav criticized Uttarakhand CM Pushkar Singh Dhami's announcement to rename 11 places across four districts. Dhami justified the renaming as honoring Indian culture and great personalities. The changes include names in Haridwar, Dehradun, Nainital, and Udham Singh Nagar. The Tapkeshwar Mahadev Temple's Acharya Dr. Vipin Joshi praised the move as aligning with Sanatan culture.
title: 'Uttarakhand ka naam bhi UP-2 kar dijiye': Akhilesh on CM Dhami renaming 11 places

description: Elon Musk has addressed paternity claims made by Ashley St. Clair, stating he is open to taking a paternity test and has provided financial support. St. Clair alleges he previously refused a test and withdrew support as manipulation. The dispute has drawn significant public attention.
title: Elon Musk breaks silence on Ashley Clair's claim of having his child: Despite ...

description: New Income Tax Slabs FY 2025-26: Starting April 1, 2025, individuals opting for the new income tax regime won't pay taxes on taxable income up to Rs 12 lakh. The revised income tax slabs for FY 2025-26 impose differentiated rates for varied income ranges with detailed tax liability calculations for incomes exceeding Rs 12 lakh.
title: Have taxable income above Rs 12 lakh? Know how it will be taxed under new regime

description: US President Trump declared that India and other US allies would soon substantially decrease their tariffs. This announcement follows his decision to implement a uniform global tariff. The move is expected to benefit US trade, correcting the current high tariffs imposed on American goods, with countries like India and the EU already showing signs of compliance.
title: 'India is going to drop tariffs substantially': Trump ahead of 'Liberation Day' deadline

description: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella praised Chinese AI company DeepSeek for its innovative AI computing architecture, highlighting its success with a team of just 200 people. DeepSeek's transformation of a research project into a top App Store product sets a new standard for Microsoft's AI efforts, emphasizing the importance of collaboration and rapid innovation.
title: Microsoft CEO to employees in Town Hall: Best thing about China's Deepseek is ...

description: Uttar Pradesh chief minister Yogi Adityanath said that the 'bulldozer model' used by his government is a necessity rather than an achievement. He justified its use for both infrastructure development and removing illegal structures. Earlier, Adityanath emphasised that law and order are upheld through these actions, and opponents must be dealt with in a language they understand to maintain justice.
title: 'Need, not an achievement': UP CM Yogi Adityanath on bulldozer action

description: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman highlighted a viral trend of AI-generated Studio Ghibli-style art featuring Prime Minister Modi. The Indian government's participation showcased key moments of Modi's tenure. Amid high demand for the tool, OpenAI has temporarily limited rates, and there is speculation about OpenAI expanding in India.
title: OpenAI CEO shares PM Modi's Ghibli photos, captioned: 'Main character?...'

description: The 7-minute workout, created by exercise physiologist Chris Jordan, is a high-intensity circuit training (HICT) routine, featuring 12 exercises performed consecutively. Each exercise lasts for 30 seconds with a 10-second break in between. This workout is suitable for all fitness levels and aims to improve both muscular strength and cardiovascular endurance, making it an attractive option for busy individuals.
title: What is the 7- minute power workout everyone's talking about?

description: A Punjab court has sentenced Bajinder Singh, a self-proclaimed pastor, to life imprisonment for a 2018 rape case. Convicted recently, Singh faced additional accusations from two more women following his conviction. The Akal Takht secretariat condemned the delay in police action and assured full support for the victims, urging them to trust in justice.
title: ‘Yeshu Yeshu prophet' Bajinder Singh sentenced to life in 2018 rape case
'Bleak future': Rahul Gandhi on Kerala’s rising drug concerns

description: Lucknow Super Giants aim for their first home victory against Punjab Kings, led by Rishabh Pant, after rebounding from a narrow loss with a win over Sunrisers Hyderabad. Key players Pooran, Marsh, and Thakur are expected to perform, with Pant under pressure to deliver a strong performance.
title: IPL match today: LSG vs PBKS in Lucknow - all you need to know
Isro images show damages caused by quake in Myanmar, see before & after pics

description: White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt highlighted high tariffs imposed by countries like India, Japan, and Canada on US goods, making exports challenging. She stressed the need for reciprocity to ensure fair treatment for American products. President Trump is set to announce significant, reciprocal tariffs soon, aimed at creating a level playing field for the United States.
title: '100% tariffs from India': White House lists tariffs imposed on US goods

description: CBSE has introduced major changes in the syllabus for the 2025-26 academic session, focusing on dynamic, student-centered learning. The updated curriculum emphasizes innovative teaching methods, including project-based and inquiry-driven learning, along with technology integration. It also revamps assessments to prioritize competency over rote memorization, aiming to equip students with critical thinking skills for real-world challenges and future careers.
title: CBSE revises Class 10 & 12 syllabus for 2025-26: Check key details here

description: OpenAI's ChatGPT gained one million users within an hour of launching a free Ghibli-style image generator. The feature, allowing users to create anime-inspired artwork, was initially for paid users and now includes limits for free-tier users due to high demand.
title: ChatGPT hits '1m users in an hour' as Ghibli image maker free version goes live

description: Uttar Pradesh chief minister Yogi Adityanath justified the ban on offering namaz on public roads, citing the Maha Kumbh's orderly conduct as a model. He emphasized the importance of discipline, noting that 66 crore devotees attended the Maha Kumbh without any incidents. This follows Meerut police's directive to restrict Eid namaz to designated areas, with heightened security measures in place.
title: 'Learn discipline from Hindus': UP CM Yogi backs ban on namaz on roads

description: Chennai Super Kings' head coach Stephen Fleming explains MS Dhoni's varying batting positions are due to physical constraints, particularly knee issues. Dhoni's role is adjusted based on game situations, balancing leadership and wicketkeeping. CSK's recent loss to Rajasthan Royals was attributed to a poor Powerplay performance and fielding errors compared to their opponents.
title: 'MS Dhoni can't bat 10 overs running full stick'

description: Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma condemned Bangladesh advisor Muhammad Yunus's claim of Bangladesh being the 'guardian' of the Indian Ocean for India's northeastern states. Yunus suggested Bangladesh as a key gateway for the region, inviting China to expand its presence.
title: 'Offensive': Assam CM's sharp retort to B'desh's Yunus' NE ‘landlocked’ remark

description: RPP senior vice-president Mishra and general secretary Rana, a member of the lower house, were remanded in custody for five days by Kathmandu district court judge Taradevi Maharjan.
title: Passports revoked, rumours swirl about treason charges against top RPP leaders in Nepal

description: Stock market today: BSE Sensex and Nifty50, the Indian equity benchmark indices, tanked in trade on Tuesday morning. While BSE Sensex plunged over 350 points, Nifty50 went below 23,450.
title: Stock market today: BSE Sensex tanks over 350 points; Nifty50 below 23,450

description: Apple's iOS 18.4 update enhances user experience with new features like Priority Notifications and Ambient Music. The Photos app receives significant upgrades, and Apple Vision Pro gains a companion app. Expanded language support and additional security fixes are also included. The update is available for iPhone XR and newer models.

description: Chennai Super Kings have had a challenging start in IPL 2025, suffering defeats against Royal Challengers Bengaluru and Rajasthan Royals after their opening win. All-rounder Ravindra Jadeja assured fans that better days are ahead, with plenty of heat coming legendary MS Dhoni's way in the last two matches.
title: Jadeja shares Insta Story dedicated to MS Dhoni after CSK's poor start

description: Sam Altman, CEO of OpenAI, received praise for sharing AI-generated Ghibli-style images of PM Modi's key moments. These images, posted by the Indian government and India Post, include Modi holding the Indian flag and diplomatic meetings with Donald Trump and Emmanuel Macron. OpenAI noted ChatGPT's rapid growth, reaching one million users in five days amidst competition from Chinese and Meta rivals.
title: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman reshares ghibli-style images of PM Modi

description: OpenAI has acquired $40 billion in new funding from SoftBank and other investors, valuing it at $300 billion. This funding will drive advancements in AI research, aiming for artificial general intelligence. The investment will also help improve OpenAI's infrastructure and expand its generative AI system amid competition from China’s DeepSeek and Meta.

description: Stock market recommendations: Motilal Oswal Financial Services recommends DLF and HDFC AMC as top stock picks for the week. DLF boasts a strong portfolio with significant pre-sales growth projected, while HDFC AMC shows potential due to its high-margin equity segment and extensive distribution network.
title: Top stocks to buy: Stock recommendations for the week starting April 1, 2025

description: In a conversation with Fox News, President Trump expressed eagerness about potentially facing Barack Obama in an election. Despite hints about a third-term run, Trump acknowledged the constitutional limitation of two terms. While he enjoys his role, his focus remains on his current term without exploring legal possibilities for another run.
title: Trump names Democrat he'd 'love' to face in 'third-term' showdown

description: Rohit Sharma and Nita Ambani were seen having a serious discussion after Mumbai Indians' win over Kolkata Knight Riders, where Rohit continued his poor form, scoring only 13 runs. Despite Sharma's struggles, MI secured an easy victory thanks to notable performances from Ashwani Kumar and Ryan Rickelton, who played a crucial role in the run chase.
title: WATCH: Rohit Sharma has intense discussion with Nita Ambani

description: ICICI Securities maintains a 'buy' recommendation on GAIL, driven by anticipated earnings recovery. Motilal Oswal keeps a 'neutral' rating on Havells India due to strong growth prospects despite pricing pressures. Emkay Global upgrades Maruti Suzuki to 'buy,' while Anand Rathi and Cantor Fitzgerald advocate buying MOIL and Adani Power due to expansion plans and valuation attractiveness, respectively.
title: Buy or sell: Stock recommendations for today

description: US President Donald Trump revealed plans to visit Qatar, UAE, and Saudi Arabia next month to strengthen ties and secure economic benefits. The visit aims to bolster security and trade relations, focusing on Saudi Arabia's pledge to invest USD 1 trillion in US companies. Additionally, Trump hinted at the possibility of seeking a third presidential term.
title: Donald Trump to visit Qatar, UAE, Saudi Arabia as early as next month

description: Starting April 1, 2025, various regulatory and financial changes, including revised income tax slabs, updated UPI regulations, and the introduction of the Unified Pension Scheme, will impact taxpayers, digital payment users, and pensioners. These changes aim to lower tax burdens, offer TDS relief, and adjust tolls, medicine, and gas prices.

No-contest clause in Ratan Tata's will, restricts sale of Tata Sons stake

description: Astronaut Sunita Williams described her view of India from space during her nine-month stay on the International Space Station. She highlighted the Himalayas' ripple effect, the fishing fleets near Mumbai and Gujarat, and the network of lights visible across the country. Williams expressed excitement about visiting her ancestral home in Gujarat.
title: What does India look like from space? Sunita Williams answers
'Will have no choice': Iran warns it may have to acquire nukes if attacked

description: 'Sikandar,' Salman Khan's eagerly awaited Eid release, hit a lukewarm reception at the box office, despite grossing Rs. 55 crore in India. The film, directed by AR Murugadoss and featuring a star-studded cast, faced tough competition from Vicky Kaushal's 'Chhaava,' which had a stronger opening earlier in the year.
title: ‘Sikandar’ box office collection: Salman and Rashmika’s film sees minimal growth on Eid

description: Swati Thapa of Rastriya Prajatantra Party advocates for restoring the constitutional monarchy, removing Nepal's federal structure, and reestablishing a Hindu state. She believes most Nepalis support these changes and criticizes foreign influences for altering Nepal's cultural identity.
title: We want our guardian back, says RPP, calls for Hindu Rashtra

description: As Trump imposes 25% additional tariffs, Indian exporters, particularly in engineering and leather goods sectors, face significant financial strain. Shipments worth $5 billion are on hold, with many US buyers demanding price adjustments or discounts. Industry leaders emphasize the need for market diversification amid uncertain trade relations with the US.
title: Exporters brace for Trump's tariffs, expect turbulence

description: Rastriya Prajatantra Party leaders Rabindra Mishra and Dhawal Shumsher Rana were remanded into custody for five days to face charges related to crimes against the state following a violent pro-monarchy protest. The incident led to widespread damage in Kathmandu, and authorities are considering similar charges against former king Gyanendra Shah.
title: Nepal lawmaker demands probe into former king's role in protests
Stage set for stormy end to Budget session as Centre plans to table bill tomorrow

description: Chandigarh Police have suspended constable Ajay Kundu after his wife Jyoti disrupted traffic to film a dance video. The viral video, captured on March 20, showed Jyoti performing at a busy intersection while her sister-in-law filmed her. Jyoti was charged with obstructing traffic and endangering public safety, though she claimed the video was shot during a red signal.
title: Chandigarh cop suspended after wife ‘stopped traffic’ to make reel

description: TikTok faces a potential shutdown in the U.S. by April 5, 2025, unless its Chinese parent company, ByteDance, sells its U.S. operations to a non-Chinese buyer. President Trump is negotiating a possible deal, with major companies like Oracle and Microsoft as potential buyers, amidst national security and geopolitical concerns.
title: TikTok ban on April 5: What law says & Donald Trump's 'China Tariff deal'
